{
  "texts": [
    "From the olfactory bulb, signals are relayed to various brain regions, including the piriform cortex, amygdala, and hippocampus (Soudry et al. 2011).",
    "This anatomical configuration facilitates robust integration of sensory information with emotional and cognitive functions.",
    "Research indicates that odors can evoke powerful memories and emotional responses due to their close relationship with the limbic system, which is critical for emotional regulation and memory formation (Daniels and Vermetten 2016).",
    "Beyond its anatomical role, the olfactory bulb also functions as a pattern recognition unit.",
    "It transforms incoming sensory input into spatial and temporal activity patterns that are characteristic of specific odorants."
  ]
}